==English==

===Alternative spellings===
*[[off-line]]

===Etymology===
[[off]] + [[line]]

===Adjective===
'''offline'''

# Describes a system which is, at the moment, not connected (generally electrically) to a larger network.  For example, a [[power plant]] which is not connected to the [[grid]], or a [[computer]] which is not connected to the [[Internet]] or to any other [[communications]] service.
#::''I printed the web pages so I could read them later when I was '''offline'''.''

===Antonyms===
*[[online]]

====Translations====
*Dutch: [[ontkoppeld]], offline
*[[Interlingua]]: [[foras de linea]], ''offline''
*Portuguese: [[fora de linha]], ''offline''
A device associated with a larger system is offline if it is under the direct control of the human. It it is available for immediate use by the system, on demand, with human intervention, but may not be operated independently of the system. 

